    "claim": "When Convex mode is enabled, `deposit()` return values are ignored and `totalCollateral()` only counts the reward-contract stake balance. If a stake call returns false or under-stakes, users are still credited collateral, but later exits try to withdraw shares that were never actually staked.",
    "impact": "Collateral can become effectively locked, liquidations can fail, and protocol accounting diverges from the real asset location/balance, which can DoS normal withdrawals and leave positions stuck.",
    "paths": [
      "A Convex booster or pool returns false / partially stakes during `_stakeUnderlying()` or `_updateConvexPool()`.",
      "The pair still credits `_userCollateralBalance` as if the full amount was staked.",
      "A later `removeCollateral*()` or `liquidate()` path calls `_unstakeUnderlying()` for the credited amount and reverts because the stake balance is lower than expected."
